Irish May external reserves rise by 300 mln punts . Ireland ' s official external reserves rose by 300 million punts to just over five billion in May , the central bank said on Thursday . " Foreign currency swaps , EU receipts and a valuation adjustment which increased the Irish pound value of the reserves contributed to this development , " the bank said in a statement . The net external liability of all credit institutions rose by 620 million in May following a large fall in April , reflecting net forward purchases of foreign currency by resident banks , the central bank said . - - Dublin Newsroom + 353 1 676 9779 
